        "timestamp": "2018-01-18 15:10:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAre there any required changes to the .drl to support the setter/getters?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "21cf9405fd7ee2256ab77100379ed49190c22eb3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3007,
          "name": "Sven van der Meer",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "svenv@vmware.com",
          "username": "vdmeer.sven"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-18 20:56:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nShould not, since Drools can access Java class properties directly (puiblic members) or as Pojo (get/set/is). Drools language/runtime stems from MVEL, which introduced that standard. \n\nCurrent documentation: https://docs.jboss.org/drools/release/7.5.0.Final/drools-docs/html_single/index.html#_property_access_on_java_beans_pojo_s\n\nI thought there is an integration test somewhere testing that, no?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "a60d5b438e5ebd49252647018fe59f6dd9220993",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-19 13:59:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nWe have JUnits that actually test the .drl - I've run across it failing on private members when I've made changes in the past. We don't explicitly set the rules as 'MVEL' - I'm curious. I guess since ONAP Jobbuilder succeeded we are ok.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
